{
    // Solution-style config for `tsc -b tsconfig.build.json` (issue #756): dependency-
    // ordered, incremental compilation of the composite @chimera/* packages off their
    // per-package tsconfig.build.json files. `tsc --build` derives the order from the
    // reference graph and skips up-to-date projects via each package's dist/.tsbuildinfo,
    // so a second run with no source changes is a no-op.
    //
    // The references mirror the acyclic, inward `workspace:*` graph (Invariant #1):
    // simulation is the zero-dep leaf; ai / networking / renderer reference it; electron
    // sits at the top (layer 2) and references simulation/ai/networking/renderer. The
    // result stays acyclic: nothing points back out to a sibling above it. The chat
    // barrel's type-only `@chimera/electron/preload/api-types` back-edge is resolved by
    // renderer/tsconfig.build.json onto electron SOURCE via a `paths` alias (NOT a
    // project reference), so it never closes a renderer → electron reference cycle.
    // `tsc --build` derives the order from the reference graph (simulation →
    // ai/networking/renderer → electron), so this list order is informational. Only
    // renderer's SCOPED component-library build participates as a partial compilation —
    // the full renderer/tactics app compilation stays on the flat `tsc --noEmit` checks
    // (renderer/tsconfig.json via the Next plugin; games/tsconfig.json for games).
    // electron joined the composite graph in F62 (#777) as a whole-package build
    // (electron/tsconfig.build.json). See the two-tier package model and the
    // source-vs-dist dual-resolution rationale in docs/architecture-overview.md §C.7.
    //
    // This file is reference-only (`files: []`) and deliberately does NOT extend the root
    // tsconfig.json — a solution config carries no compilerOptions of its own.
    "files": [],
    "references": [
        { "path": "./simulation/tsconfig.build.json" },
        { "path": "./ai/tsconfig.build.json" },
        { "path": "./networking/tsconfig.build.json" },
        { "path": "./renderer/tsconfig.build.json" },
        { "path": "./electron/tsconfig.build.json" }
    ]
}
